### ClickNBack — Workflow 5: Admin Purchase Confirmation (Manual Approval)
###
### Goal: Review pending purchases and either confirm or reverse them.
### Role: Admin
###
### Prerequisites:
###   - At least one user with a pending purchase (Workflow 3).
###   - Admin credentials (e.g., carol@clicknback.com / Str0ng!Pass).
###
### How to run:
###   1. Open this file in VS Code with the REST Client extension installed.
###   2. Run Step 1 to log in as admin.
###   3. Run Step 2 to list pending purchases.
###   4. Copy a purchase ID and run Step 3 (confirm) or Step 4 (reverse).
###
### NOTE: These endpoints are in backlog and not yet implemented.
###       The requests below document the intended API contract.
###
### Live API: https://clicknback.com
### Docs:     https://clicknback.com/docs

@baseUrl = https://clicknback.com


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 1 — Login as admin
#
# Expected: 200 OK with an access_token.
# Copy the access_token value and set @adminToken below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "carol@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}


###

@adminToken = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 2 — List all pending purchases
#
# Filters purchases by status="pending" to show those awaiting admin review.
# Expected: 200 OK with a paginated list of pending purchases.
# Copy a purchase `id` value and set @purchaseId below.
#
# Business rules:
#   - Only pending purchases appear. Confirmed/reversed purchases are filtered out.
#   - List is paginated; adjust page and page_size as needed.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases?status=pending&page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###

@purchaseId = PASTE_PURCHASE_ID_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3 — View a single purchase (optional details check)
#
# Expected: 200 OK with full purchase details including amount, merchant, date,
#           user, and current status.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases/{{purchaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 4 — Confirm a purchase
#
# Manually confirms a pending purchase. On success:
#   - Purchase status changes to "confirmed"
#   - PurchaseConfirmed event is published
#   - Cashback is calculated and credited to the user's wallet (pending balance)
#
# Expected: 200 OK with the updated purchase including status: "confirmed"
#           and the calculated cashback_amount.
#
# Business rules:
#   - Can only confirm if status is "pending". Attempting to confirm an already-confirmed
#     or reversed purchase returns 409 Conflict.
#   - Cashback is calculated based on the active offer for the merchant on the
#     purchase date, subject to the user's monthly cap.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 5 — Reverse a purchase (alternative to confirm)
#
# Manually reverses a purchase, e.g., due to dispute, user request, or fraud.
# On success:
#   - Purchase status changes to "reversed"
#   - PurchaseReversed event is published
#   - If the purchase was previously confirmed (and cashback was credited),
#     the cashback is debited from the user's wallet.
#   - If the purchase was still pending (no cashback credited yet), no wallet impact.
#
# Expected: 200 OK with the updated purchase including status: "reversed"
#           and cashback_amount reset to 0.
#
# Business rules:
#   - Can reverse a pending or confirmed purchase.
#   - Cannot reverse an already-reversed purchase (returns 409 Conflict).
#   - Wallet impact: if previously confirmed, cashback is debited.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/reverse
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 6 — Check the updated purchase (verify confirmation/reversal)
#
# After confirming or reversing, fetch the purchase again to verify the
# status change and any cashback amount.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases/{{purchaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 7 — Check the user's wallet (optional, to see impact)
#
# After confirming, the user's wallet will show pending cashback.
# After reversing, pending cashback decreases.
#
# You'll need the user_id from the purchase (see Step 3).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/USER_ID_HERE/wallet
# Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
